1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,100
(The following content may not be
suitable for viewers under 15.)

2
00:00:03,100 --> 00:00:04,480
(Viewer discretion is advised.)

3
00:00:10,100 --> 00:00:11,170
What was that?

4
00:00:15,070 --> 00:00:18,340
You almost cracked your head open.

5
00:00:19,740 --> 00:00:22,010
That's why you should've listened.

6
00:00:23,450 --> 00:00:24,450
Fine.

7
00:00:27,680 --> 00:00:30,950
Do you want to go get something to eat?

8
00:00:34,320 --> 00:00:35,660
What do you want to eat?

9
00:00:38,490 --> 00:00:39,560
Steamed buns?

10
00:00:50,170 --> 00:00:51,570
It isn't monsoon season.

11
00:00:52,010 --> 00:00:54,210
Why is it raining so much in the fall?

12
00:00:54,540 --> 00:00:55,580
I know.

13
00:01:01,580 --> 00:01:02,620
Thanks,

14
00:01:04,020 --> 00:01:05,090
Jung Hee.

15
00:01:06,820 --> 00:01:08,360
For coming to get me.

16
00:01:09,690 --> 00:01:11,230
This is friendship.

17
00:01:11,830 --> 00:01:15,430
You're on probation
because of me after all.

18
00:01:16,530 --> 00:01:18,130
I'm a girl of loyalty.

19
00:01:23,270 --> 00:01:26,340
You look better with the
tape on your glasses.

20
00:01:26,710 --> 00:01:27,810
It looks fashionable.

21
00:01:28,640 --> 00:01:29,680
Really?

22
00:01:30,610 --> 00:01:31,950
Do you think it'll become a trend?

23
00:01:32,780 --> 00:01:33,880
A little?

24
00:01:34,480 --> 00:01:35,550
A little?

25
00:02:00,610 --> 00:02:01,810
What was that?

26
00:02:06,980 --> 00:02:08,020
Sorry.

27
00:02:10,090 --> 00:02:11,420
That hurts.

28
00:02:11,420 --> 00:02:13,890
- Hey.
- Let go. That hurts.

29
00:02:13,890 --> 00:02:14,960
That hurts.

30
00:02:18,030 --> 00:02:19,130
What?

31
00:02:20,700 --> 00:02:22,830
What is it? Let go.

32
00:02:37,280 --> 00:02:38,280
What did you say?

33
00:02:40,820 --> 00:02:41,950
Must you...

34
00:02:43,750 --> 00:02:45,290
Must you do this?

35
00:02:46,020 --> 00:02:48,120
How can I live without you?

36
00:02:49,390 --> 00:02:50,860
Of course you can live.

37
00:02:51,360 --> 00:02:53,230
You'll be fine.

38
00:02:53,960 --> 00:02:56,230
Thank you for everything.

39
00:02:57,200 --> 00:02:59,270
You were nice to a nobody like me.

40
00:02:59,270 --> 00:03:00,300
No.

41
00:03:01,070 --> 00:03:02,140
Do Ha.

42
00:03:03,610 --> 00:03:06,840
Please be good to your wife.

43
00:03:07,840 --> 00:03:09,810
You should forget about me.

44
00:03:26,660 --> 00:03:27,730
Jung Hee.

45
00:03:29,500 --> 00:03:30,570
Are you all right?

46
00:03:33,500 --> 00:03:34,570
Jung Hee.

47
00:03:39,770 --> 00:03:41,680
- Happy?
- Don't hit Jung Hee!

48
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:43,480
Stop it!

49
00:03:44,980 --> 00:03:47,680
Jung Hee, how is your mom's hand?

50
00:03:47,680 --> 00:03:49,980
Mom, did you hurt your hand?

51
00:03:49,980 --> 00:03:52,720
What are you saying? Are you sleeping?

52
00:03:56,990 --> 00:03:58,290
How...

53
00:03:59,560 --> 00:04:01,430
Hey, Jung Hee.

54
00:04:03,060 --> 00:04:04,400
This is my guess.

55
00:04:04,400 --> 00:04:06,670
Adults must have...

56
00:04:07,100 --> 00:04:09,140
lives of their own.

57
00:04:10,370 --> 00:04:13,140
They can't control their feelings either.

58
00:04:13,140 --> 00:04:14,540
Their own lives?

59
00:04:15,780 --> 00:04:17,510
They're always ordering us
because they're adults.

60
00:04:17,510 --> 00:04:19,180
They stomp over us.

61
00:04:19,850 --> 00:04:21,420
I can't forgive him.

62
00:04:22,250 --> 00:04:24,090
Never!

63
00:04:34,400 --> 00:04:35,560
Drink some water.

64
00:05:03,090 --> 00:05:04,560
Do you have to pee?

65
00:05:05,590 --> 00:05:08,100
Why are you staring at the bedpan?

66
00:05:09,730 --> 00:05:11,700
Did you do something wrong again?

67
00:05:15,200 --> 00:05:16,400
I'm back.

68
00:05:16,770 --> 00:05:18,310
Did you get caught in the rain?

69
00:05:18,310 --> 00:05:19,940
You should always take an umbrella.

70
00:05:19,940 --> 00:05:21,640
It was just a little bit.

71
00:05:22,640 --> 00:05:24,680
Jung Hee, were you out?

72
00:05:28,480 --> 00:05:30,420
What's wrong?

73
00:05:30,820 --> 00:05:33,020
Are you crazy?

74
00:05:33,020 --> 00:05:36,020
Why are you looking at Do Ha like that?

75
00:05:37,160 --> 00:05:38,390
What a bother.

76
00:05:38,790 --> 00:05:40,130
Do Ha, let's go cook.

77
00:05:40,530 --> 00:05:41,630
Okay.

78
00:05:42,400 --> 00:05:43,530
Auntie.

79
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:45,830
Yes?

80
00:05:57,310 --> 00:06:00,720
Jung Hee, did something happen at school?

81
00:06:02,320 --> 00:06:03,850
Is it because of Jin?

82
00:06:03,850 --> 00:06:05,090
Auntie.

83
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:15,660
I got yelled at school because of you...

84
00:06:15,900 --> 00:06:17,600
for wearing this.

85
00:06:19,930 --> 00:06:22,070
Really? What do I do?

86
00:06:22,300 --> 00:06:24,370
I'm sorry.

87
00:06:24,440 --> 00:06:27,110
I thought you wanted to wear it.

88
00:06:27,710 --> 00:06:30,250
Did they hit you? Did you have a drill?

89
00:06:33,150 --> 00:06:34,220
What about this?

90
00:06:35,050 --> 00:06:37,620
I asked you to alter it ages ago.

91
00:06:39,320 --> 00:06:40,520
What about this?

92
00:06:40,590 --> 00:06:43,730
You said you would wash this.

93
00:06:44,430 --> 00:06:46,690
What about this and this?

94
00:06:49,700 --> 00:06:51,130
I'm sorry, Jung Hee.

95
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:53,000
There's a lot of work at
the factory because...

96
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:55,870
If you're not going to do work,

97
00:06:55,870 --> 00:06:57,710
go back to your home.

98
00:07:02,110 --> 00:07:04,010
I hate you.

99
00:07:08,920 --> 00:07:10,420
I'm sorry, Jung Hee.

100
00:07:23,100 --> 00:07:24,200
Jung Hee.

101
00:07:27,770 --> 00:07:29,800
- Hae Joo.
- Jung Hee.

102
00:07:29,870 --> 00:07:31,570
What happened?

103
00:07:31,570 --> 00:07:33,410
Why didn't you come to school?

104
00:07:35,010 --> 00:07:36,280
Hello.

105
00:07:37,180 --> 00:07:39,280
- Come to my room.
- Jung Hee.

106
00:07:39,880 --> 00:07:40,880
Hey...

107
00:07:41,480 --> 00:07:44,450
Your father will be home in a while.

108
00:07:44,450 --> 00:07:46,390
- Mom.
- Come on, Mom.

109
00:07:46,390 --> 00:07:47,390
Be quiet.

110
00:07:47,390 --> 00:07:48,790
I'll leave soon.

111
00:07:49,520 --> 00:07:50,790
I'm sorry.

112
00:07:54,030 --> 00:07:56,870
Why did she come here
with a kid on her back?

113
00:07:56,870 --> 00:07:59,370
Mom, don't be like that.

114
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:01,340
Be quiet, you jerk.

115
00:08:04,910 --> 00:08:08,110
Jin's contact in Seoul?

116
00:08:09,810 --> 00:08:10,880
Actually,

117
00:08:12,350 --> 00:08:13,650
my dad...

118
00:08:14,680 --> 00:08:17,450
was arrested and is in Seoul.

119
00:08:17,450 --> 00:08:18,650
What?

120
00:08:20,120 --> 00:08:21,360
Why?

121
00:08:21,360 --> 00:08:23,690
He got involved in current
state of affairs.

122
00:08:24,330 --> 00:08:26,490
I can't visit him.

123
00:08:27,060 --> 00:08:29,030
- It's frustrating.
- Then...

124
00:08:29,760 --> 00:08:31,600
were you in Seoul all this time?

125
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:32,600
Yes.

126
00:08:33,570 --> 00:08:36,770
I was asking around.

127
00:08:37,440 --> 00:08:40,640
I tried asking relatives for help, but...

128
00:08:45,110 --> 00:08:46,480
Why are you taking...

129
00:08:47,450 --> 00:08:48,820
Eng Cho around?

130
00:08:51,250 --> 00:08:54,360
Young Choon is also at the police station.

131
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:58,260
There's no one to take care of her.

132
00:08:58,260 --> 00:08:59,830
But, still...

133
00:09:06,270 --> 00:09:07,670
Hello.

134
00:09:13,110 --> 00:09:15,040
Shim Ae Sook.

135
00:09:17,510 --> 00:09:19,380
- You look pretty today.
- Hey.

136
00:09:20,450 --> 00:09:21,980
What do you want me to do?

137
00:09:22,280 --> 00:09:23,590
What should I do...

138
00:09:23,790 --> 00:09:25,950
for them to release Young Choon?

139
00:09:27,290 --> 00:09:28,420
If I tell you,

140
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:30,360
will you do it?

141
00:09:34,460 --> 00:09:36,870
Ae Sook. Both you and I...

142
00:09:37,170 --> 00:09:38,600
are nobodies.

143
00:09:39,330 --> 00:09:40,940
There's nothing we can do.

144
00:09:51,610 --> 00:09:52,980
You were alive?

145
00:09:55,020 --> 00:09:57,050
Because of your Dad's case,

146
00:09:57,350 --> 00:09:59,990
he had to find something
to report to his superior.

147
00:10:00,760 --> 00:10:03,460
Young Choon was unlucky.

148
00:10:04,860 --> 00:10:06,690
Because he helped your father,

149
00:10:07,560 --> 00:10:09,400
they call him a communist.

150
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:10,930
Young Choon...

151
00:10:13,640 --> 00:10:15,570
only did what he did
because I asked for help.

152
00:10:15,570 --> 00:10:17,310
Even if you say that, it won't help.

153
00:10:18,310 --> 00:10:19,440
They won't care.

154
00:10:20,110 --> 00:10:21,210
I don't know...

155
00:10:22,010 --> 00:10:23,140
anything more than that.

156
00:10:29,650 --> 00:10:30,690
Ae Sook.

157
00:10:32,290 --> 00:10:33,460
Thank you.

158
00:10:43,570 --> 00:10:45,170
I'll pick it up.

159
00:10:47,800 --> 00:10:48,970
This is Seongbuk-dong.

160
00:10:51,640 --> 00:10:52,710
Hello?

161
00:10:54,540 --> 00:10:55,610
Hello?

162
00:10:58,810 --> 00:10:59,880
Hello.

163
00:11:06,450 --> 00:11:08,920
It's me. Jin.

164
00:11:09,260 --> 00:11:12,460
I'm sorry I called you out of the blue.

165
00:11:12,490 --> 00:11:13,800
I thought...

166
00:11:15,930 --> 00:11:20,340
maybe you might be able to help me.

167
00:11:21,570 --> 00:11:24,370
Let's dance

168
00:11:24,740 --> 00:11:27,940
Before the night ends

169
00:11:29,040 --> 00:11:31,180
- Boogie woogie - Dad.

170
00:11:31,180 --> 00:11:32,910
Boogie woogie

171
00:11:34,620 --> 00:11:35,650
Who is that?

172
00:11:36,850 --> 00:11:39,820
It's Jung Hee. Gosh, Jung Hee.

173
00:11:39,820 --> 00:11:41,390
My daughter, Jung Hee.

174
00:11:41,720 --> 00:11:43,460
My smart Jung Hee.

175
00:11:45,630 --> 00:11:47,900
- Gosh.
- Sir.

176
00:11:47,900 --> 00:11:51,200
- Dad.
- What, what, what?

177
00:11:51,300 --> 00:11:53,270
Do you want allowance?

178
00:11:53,270 --> 00:11:54,440
Hold on.

179
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:58,070
Let's see. Where's my wallet?

180
00:11:58,070 --> 00:11:59,240
Mom!

181
00:11:59,810 --> 00:12:01,280
Dad's home!

182
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:03,680
Mom!

183
00:12:05,050 --> 00:12:06,480
I know, stupid girl.

184
00:12:07,550 --> 00:12:10,850
I can't find my wallet. Where did it go?

185
00:12:10,850 --> 00:12:12,020
Get up!

186
00:12:12,090 --> 00:12:14,220
- Who is this?
- Get up.

187
00:12:15,160 --> 00:12:17,660
Who else would it be? Get up.

188
00:12:17,660 --> 00:12:20,430
I have to give Jung Hee some allowance.

189
00:12:22,400 --> 00:12:23,800
My goodness.

190
00:12:23,870 --> 00:12:24,900
Go inside.

191
00:12:34,980 --> 00:12:36,610
Jung Hee...

192
00:12:40,050 --> 00:12:41,880
- Hey, Duk Seon.
- Hello.

193
00:12:41,880 --> 00:12:43,950
Your skirt keeps on getting shorter.

194
00:12:46,490 --> 00:12:47,560
Hae Joo.

195
00:12:49,720 --> 00:12:53,330
I'm sorry I missed so many classes, sir.

196
00:12:56,630 --> 00:12:59,430
Come to the office before we start class.

197
00:12:59,670 --> 00:13:00,740
Okay.

198
00:13:03,040 --> 00:13:04,310
It's Hae Joo!

199
00:13:04,440 --> 00:13:05,640
- Hae Joo!
- Hae Joo!

200
00:13:05,640 --> 00:13:07,940
- Hey, keep it down!
- Hello.

201
00:13:08,240 --> 00:13:10,810
Hey, where have you been?

202
00:13:10,810 --> 00:13:12,150
- We were worried.
- Where were you?

203
00:13:12,150 --> 00:13:13,350
Are you okay?

204
00:13:17,550 --> 00:13:18,590
Hey.

205
00:13:19,720 --> 00:13:21,360
I heard about your father.

206
00:13:22,490 --> 00:13:23,960
You must be heartbroken.

207
00:13:25,660 --> 00:13:27,830
You must brace yourself
at times like these.

208
00:13:30,470 --> 00:13:33,070
Stay focused, Park Hae Joo!

209
00:13:34,070 --> 00:13:37,240
Don't influence the other kids.

210
00:13:37,510 --> 00:13:39,110
- Do you understand?
- Yes.

211
00:13:51,150 --> 00:13:52,850
- I was so annoyed.
- Hello.

212
00:13:53,660 --> 00:13:54,890
Isn't that Jin?

213
00:13:54,890 --> 00:13:57,230
- Hello.
- It really is Jin.

214
00:13:57,330 --> 00:13:58,990
What is he doing here?

215
00:13:59,560 --> 00:14:00,860
I'll get going first.

216
00:14:04,900 --> 00:14:05,930
Jin.

217
00:14:06,170 --> 00:14:08,140
Jung Hee, have you been well?

218
00:14:10,310 --> 00:14:11,710
You must be here to see Hae Joo.

219
00:14:12,370 --> 00:14:13,410
Yes.

220
00:14:14,340 --> 00:14:15,610
I also thought I should see you...

221
00:14:16,610 --> 00:14:18,380
I see Hae Joo coming.

222
00:14:18,750 --> 00:14:19,880
Hae Joo!

223
00:14:31,960 --> 00:14:33,230
Why did you come here?

224
00:14:33,360 --> 00:14:35,960
Eng Cho is doing fine.

225
00:14:36,870 --> 00:14:37,900
Eng Cho...

226
00:14:39,230 --> 00:14:42,040
will be taken away by an orphanage.
Actually,

227
00:14:43,770 --> 00:14:45,640
she's not my real sister.

228
00:14:46,740 --> 00:14:48,880
I kept her with me because
she was homeless.

229
00:14:49,840 --> 00:14:53,050
I'll keep Eng Cho with me.

230
00:14:53,150 --> 00:14:55,420
- I can take care of her.
- Why?

231
00:14:55,580 --> 00:14:57,320
You don't have anything to do with us.

232
00:14:58,490 --> 00:14:59,790
I told you before.

233
00:14:59,920 --> 00:15:03,360
You need to stay focused.
Watch out for yourself.

234
00:15:06,060 --> 00:15:07,400
I'm finished.

235
00:15:08,460 --> 00:15:10,030
I'll wait for you, Young Choon.

236
00:15:22,340 --> 00:15:25,050
Hae Joo, did you meet him?

237
00:15:25,610 --> 00:15:27,320
How did Young Choon look?

238
00:15:30,250 --> 00:15:31,490
Hae Joo.

239
00:15:49,270 --> 00:15:51,840
You should get going.

240
00:15:52,440 --> 00:15:53,580
I'll go home too.

241
00:15:54,680 --> 00:15:56,010
Let's walk a little more.

242
00:15:57,010 --> 00:15:58,410
I'm okay.

243
00:15:59,350 --> 00:16:01,680
- You should go.
- In a bit.

244
00:16:02,550 --> 00:16:03,690
Let's walk together.

245
00:16:12,290 --> 00:16:13,400
Dong Moon.

246
00:16:14,230 --> 00:16:15,560
Are you going to my place?

247
00:16:16,060 --> 00:16:18,100
Dong Moon, it's been a while.

248
00:16:18,470 --> 00:16:19,570
Have you been well?

249
00:16:20,670 --> 00:16:23,770
- What are you doing here?
- He came to see Hae Joo.

250
00:16:23,770 --> 00:16:25,040
I missed Jung Hee.

251
00:16:25,970 --> 00:16:29,780
No, it's not true. Hae
Joo asked for his help.

252
00:16:36,680 --> 00:16:40,050
Then you can go after seeing Jung Hee.

253
00:16:46,390 --> 00:16:47,800
Dong Moon!

254
00:16:48,860 --> 00:16:49,930
Bae Dong Moon.

255
00:16:50,470 --> 00:16:51,830
He's still cute.

256
00:16:55,500 --> 00:16:57,810
- Do you want to go now?
- Yes.

257
00:16:58,810 --> 00:17:00,340
Take care on your way back home.

258
00:17:03,210 --> 00:17:06,110
Dong Moon! Wait for me.

259
00:17:08,180 --> 00:17:09,350
Why are you coming already?

260
00:17:09,820 --> 00:17:12,050
Didn't you miss him? You
should talk with him.

261
00:17:12,120 --> 00:17:13,820
We talked enough already.

262
00:17:13,920 --> 00:17:15,890
Also, he's here to see Hae Joo.

263
00:17:15,920 --> 00:17:17,290
Hae Joo asked him for a favor.

264
00:17:17,430 --> 00:17:18,990
You know Young Choon from
the pharmacy, right?

265
00:17:19,060 --> 00:17:22,500
He's arrested, but he couldn't get...

266
00:17:22,500 --> 00:17:23,530
Jung Hee.

267
00:17:23,970 --> 00:17:25,000
Yes?

268
00:17:25,800 --> 00:17:27,340
You don't have to make up excuses.

269
00:17:28,170 --> 00:17:30,570
It's not an excuse. It's the truth.

270
00:17:30,570 --> 00:17:33,010
Why would I make an excuse to you?

271
00:17:34,810 --> 00:17:35,880
That's true.

272
00:17:37,410 --> 00:17:39,580
We don't need excuses between us.

273
00:17:40,620 --> 00:17:41,750
I'll get going.

274
00:17:42,250 --> 00:17:44,890
Dong Moon! Bae Dong Moon!

275
00:17:51,990 --> 00:17:53,560
Are you home, Jung Hee?

276
00:17:55,360 --> 00:17:56,430
Jung Hee.

277
00:17:56,560 --> 00:17:59,030
Are you craving any dishes?

278
00:17:59,200 --> 00:18:00,370
If you want anything, I'll make it for you.

279
00:18:00,370 --> 00:18:01,840
I don't want anything.

280
00:18:02,300 --> 00:18:05,910
You like dried whitebait
and pork jangjorim, right?

281
00:18:06,910 --> 00:18:08,040
Forget it.

282
00:18:08,680 --> 00:18:10,810
It's so busy I'm going to go crazy.

283
00:18:11,310 --> 00:18:13,550
Number three quit.

284
